        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This commit is preventing the build from working in MacPorts due to:\r\n\r\n```\r\nCMake Error at cmake/FindLpeg.cmake:8 (message):\r\n  lpeg library found at /opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.so but built as a bundle\r\n  rather than a dylib, please rebuild with `-dynamiclib` rather than\r\n  `-bundle`\r\n```\r\n\r\nTwo libs are installed in the MacPorts' prefix of `/opt/local`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.dylib\r\n/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.so\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe output of `otool` for these two files is:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ otool -hv \"/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.dylib\"\r\n/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.dylib:\r\nMach header\r\n      magic  cputype cpusubtype  caps    filetype ncmds sizeofcmds      flags\r\nMH_MAGIC_64    ARM64        ALL  0x00       DYLIB    15       1400   NOUNDEFS DYLDLINK TWOLEVEL NO_REEXPORTED_DYLIBS\r\n\r\n$ otool -hv \"/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.so\"\r\n/opt/local/lib/lua/5.1/lpeg.so:\r\nMach header\r\n      magic  cputype cpusubtype  caps    filetype ncmds sizeofcmds      flags\r\nMH_MAGIC_64    ARM64        ALL  0x00      BUNDLE    14       1336   NOUNDEFS DYLDLINK TWOLEVEL\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy question is would changing the order of the `find_library2` paths be sufficient to correct this so that searching for `lpeg.so` would come after searching for `lpeg${CMAKE_SHARED_LIBRARY_SUFFIX}`?\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n-find_library2(LPEG_LIBRARY NAMES lpeg_a lpeg liblpeg_a lpeg.so lpeg${CMAKE_SHARED_LIBRARY_SUFFIX} PATH_SUFFIXES lua/5.1)\r\n+find_library2(LPEG_LIBRARY NAMES lpeg_a lpeg liblpeg_a lpeg${CMAKE_SHARED_LIBRARY_SUFFIX} lpeg.so PATH_SUFFIXES lua/5.1)\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2025-02-25T17:30:33Z",
