        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> My question is would changing the order of the find_library2 paths be sufficient to correct\r\n\r\nTheoretically no, but probably yes in practice (it's undefined, so it can be different for each platform). The proper way to enforce order is to just make two calls to `find_library` with the first call being the higher priority.",
